Sherri,<br>
     I am so touched by your words.  It is important to get the perspective of someone who has walked in your shoes - I've had to keep all of this to myself, because my friends and family don't have any understanding of PTSD and advise me to &quot;dump him&quot;.  I know what I am doing, I'm strong enough to handle it (though at 19 I would never have had the inner tools necessary to persevere), but I sometimes feel so alone and need emotional support and advise from someone who's experienced what he's experienced or another woman who's felt as lost as I have from time to time.  I know that what I am experiencing is nothing compared to what he is going through day to day...I'm in this by choice, he doesn't have one. Thank you for sharing your open heart with me...
